{"type":"message","timestamp":"2026-07-22T16:33:29.387Z","session_id":"ses_07553377dffevhWu0pVHW1vkE5","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Here is how Formal AI works, grounded in its own source, data, and tests: across 5 topics with 13 citations, every claim points at a real artifact — source files content-addressed through the owned manifest, the data artifacts they generate, and the tests that lock the behaviour — rather than prose docs. The answer is a deterministic function of the embedded source, so it cannot cite anything the repository does not ship.\n\nGenerated document (how-formal-ai-works.lino):\n\nsystem_explanation\n  engine meta_language\n  question \"how does Formal AI work?\"\n  source_file_count 292\n  source_manifest_content_id \"source_tree_464f1031f611befc\"\n  section_count 5\n  citation_count 13\n  sections\n    section\n      topic \"deterministic_meta_algorithm\"\n      statement \"Formal AI answers agentic requests with a deterministic planner state machine: a keyword-routed recipe walk (write, verify, final answer), never neural inference, so every step is a reproducible function of its inputs.\"\n      citations\n        citation\n          kind source\n          path \"src/agentic_coding/planner.rs\"\n          content_id \"source_module_600879e2bb22a203\"\n        citation\n          kind source\n          path \"src/agentic_coding/mod.rs\"\n          content_id \"source_module_aca1c8b8f52e8ae8\"\n    section\n      topic \"source_to_links_round_trip\"\n      statement \"The entire owned source tree is embedded as content-addressed data and projected through the single CST/AST engine (tree-sitter); every owned module round-trips source to links and back byte-for-byte, so the system's own code is present in its data as links.\"\n      citations\n        citation\n          kind source\n          path \"src/self_source_links.rs\"\n          content_id \"source_module_2331204f81670611\"\n        citation\n          kind source\n          path \"src/agentic_coding/self_ast.rs\"\n          content_id \"source_module_9104c8097027e9ae\"\n        citation\n          kind test\n          path \"tests/unit/issue_558_source_links.rs\"\n    section\n      topic \"self_healing_loop\"\n      statement \"When Formal AI cannot answer, it does not simply fail: it captures the failure as a structured RepairCase (unknown trace, a verified source-to-links mapping, and a benchmark gate) that never advances past awaiting human review.\"\n      citations\n        citation\n          kind source\n          path \"src/self_healing.rs\"\n          content_id \"source_module_444e90593e01e8e0\"\n        citation\n          kind data\n          path \"data/meta/self-healing-case.lino\"\n        citation\n          kind test\n          path \"tests/unit/issue_558_self_healing.rs\"\n    section\n      topic \"human_gated_promotion_ledger\"\n      statement \"An approved lesson is promoted into a durable learning ledger only when the benchmark gate is green and a human approves; a repeated failure is then answered from the ledger instead of being re-derived, which is the concrete payoff of auto learning.\"\n      citations\n        citation\n          kind source\n          path \"src/learning_ledger.rs\"\n          content_id \"source_module_b3603c2c577cd078\"\n        citation\n          kind data\n          path \"data/meta/learning-ledger.lino\"\n        citation\n          kind test\n          path \"tests/unit/issue_558_learning_ledger.rs\"\n    section\n      topic \"agentic_interface\"\n      statement \"Every capability is reachable over the OpenAI-compatible agentic interface used by external CLIs (Codex, OpenCode, Gemini, Agent CLI), driven by the same deterministic planner and proven over the wire by server integration tests.\"\n      citations\n        citation\n          kind source\n          path \"src/agentic_coding/driver.rs\"\n          content_id \"source_module_24c3e8c46a44d30e\"\n        citation\n          kind test\n          path \"tests/integration/issue_558_learning_ledger.rs\""}]}
